Hurricane Rita strengthened to a category two storm with winds of 160 km/h, threatening the Gulf of Mexico.
OPEC pledged to increase oil production, causing prices to drop despite the storm's approach.
Airlines suspended flights, and evacuations were ordered in Florida and Louisiana.
New Orleans prepared for another evacuation as Rita neared.
Texas also braced for impact, moving Katrina survivors to safety.
Rita's path could lead to a Category 4 hurricane, prompting widespread evacuations.
The situation remains critical as authorities monitor the storm's progress towards the vulnerable Gulf Coast.
